snippet.textDisplay: As a lifelong PJ fan who has seen them in concert 20 times and taken trips to go see them I can say that their best days as a recording band are definitely behind them. I feel their last good record was "Backspacer". I hope this new album delivers. PJ is one of the greatest and most giving live acts of all time and still are. Eddie's voice is still very strong. But if I'm being honest the creative juices don't seem like they are really there anymore. Just glad they are still together. I think the fact that they didn't tour themselves to death and gave each other space probably added to their longevity. As did staying away from the worst drugs.
